RACE.FOOTNOTES: RB MARY LYLAH stalk the pace early from the four path, then advanced in late backstretch to vie for the lead with inner foes into the turn, then kicked clear at the top of the bend and was ridden out to the wire to score easily. HONEY PROOF led the way early along the inside, was met with outer foes to vie for the lead down the late backstretch and into the turn, then was out kicked by RB MARY LYLAH and held the place position in the end. TM PURNCESS tracked the pace while three wide and between rivals in the early backstretch then moved up to battle between rivals heading into the turn, was used up then flattened out in the stretch. UPTOWN RINGOFFIRE was unhurried early, then settled inside and passed tired foes in the home stretch. RB BLAIR HOPE tracked the pace from the inside, bumped WMA SMOKE SIGNAL mid backstretch, then bid from the three path on the turn and came empty in the end. WMA SMOKE SIGNAL tracked the pace from the two path, was bumped mid backstretch, then bid on the turn and was no threat.
